getObject

public final Object getObject()
Returns the value corresponding to this ResourceBundleKey.

This method never returns null.

This method calls getResourceBundle(). If the return value is null, then the return value of getKey() is returned. Otherwise, the result of calling ResourceBundle.getObject(String) on the returned ResourceBundle supplying it with the key is returned.

Returns:
a non-null Object representing the value corresponding to this ResourceBundleKey

valueOf

public static final ResourceBundleKey valueOf(ResourceBundle defaultResourceBundle,
                                              Locale locale,
                                              ResourceBundle.Control control,
                                              String key)
Returns a new ResourceBundleKey that is appropriate for the supplied key.

This method never returns null.

The supplied key is checked to see if it is null. If so, an IllegalArgumentException is thrown.

Next, the key is trimmed and then parsed into a maximum of two components:

  1. A bundle name component. A bundle name is a String of the form normally supplied to ResourceBundle.getBundle(String, Locale, ClassLoader, Control)—that is, a fully-qualified class name whose segments are separated with periods (".").
  2. A key component, separated from the bundle name with a solidus ("/"). A key is an arbitrary String that is legal for supplying to the ResourceBundle.getObject(String) method.

The bundle name component of the supplied key is optional. In this case, if the supplied and trimmed key begins with a solidus ("/"), then the remainder of the key is taken to be a key that is contained by the supplied defaultResourceBundle parameter.

If for any reason the supplied key cannot be parsed into a (possibly empty) bundle name and key component divided by a solidus:

  • The code checks to see if the supplied ResourceBundle contains the trimmed key.
  • If it does, then the equivalent of new ResourceBundleKey(defaultResourceBundle, key.trim()) is returned. If it does not, then the equivalent of new ResourceBundleKey(key.trim()) is returned.

Parameters:
defaultResourceBundle - the ResourceBundle that is used to resolve relative keys; may be null
locale - the Locale to use when loading ResourceBundles; if null then the return value of Locale.getDefault() is used instead
control - the ResourceBundle.Control to use when loading ResourceBundles; if null then the return value of Control.getControl(Control.FORMAT_DEFAULT) is used instead
key - the key to parse; must not be null
Returns:
a new ResourceBundleKey; never null
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if key is null
MissingResourceException - if a ResourceBundle could not be loaded or a resource within a ResourceBundle could not be found
